headline.print_headline: Bombings in Iraqi Capital Kill at Least 23 People
headline.main: Bombings in Iraqi Capital Kill at Least 23 People

docs.snippet: A wave of explosions rocked mainly Shiite neighborhoods in Baghdad shortly after sunset on Monday, killing at least 23 people and wounding dozens, officials said....
docs.lead_paragraph: A wave of explosions rocked mainly Shiite neighborhoods in Baghdad shortly after sunset on Monday, killing at least 23 people and wounding dozens, officials said.

headline.print_headline: Afghan Taliban Shot Dead in Pakistan's Northwest
headline.main: Afghan Taliban Shot Dead in Pakistan's Northwest

docs.snippet: A former Afghan Taliban minister who was among a powerful faction of the Taliban calling for direct talks with President Hamid Karzai's government was shot and killed Monday in Pakistan's northwest city of Peshawar, on the border with Afghanistan....
docs.lead_paragraph: A former Afghan Taliban minister who was among a powerful faction of the Taliban calling for direct talks with President Hamid Karzai's government was shot and killed Monday in Pakistan's northwest city of Peshawar, on the border with Afghanistan.
